y traffic regulations and laws the Hirer shall pay all fines and penalties which may be incurred including any fines and penalties imposed by law on owners of a vehicle and shall be liable for all Summon Notices and inquiries in connection therewith. The Hirer shall indemnify the Owner for any fines or penalties or expenses paid by the Owner for any breaches of traffic regulations and rules by the Hirer or his driver.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="rental col-md-12 col-xs-12">\r\n<div class="para"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n<div class="policy-txt">8.The Hirer is solely responsible for any Area Licence Fee payable for entry into the Restricted Zone of the city during operation hours.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="rental col-md-12 col-xs-12">\r\n	<div class="para"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n	<div class="policy-txt">\r\n	<div>\r\n	9. (a) The Vehicle shall not be overloaded and shall at all times, at the Hirer''s expense, be provided with sufficient oil, water and the prescribed\r\n	tyre pressure. When not in use, the Vehicle must be properly parked and locked. The Hirer shall not tamper with the speedometer and in the event of the same not functioning properly, the Hirer shall immediately inform the Owner of the defect; whereupon the Owner shall provide the Hirer with a name and address of a workshop whereby the Hirer shall deliver the Vehicle so as to remedy the defect immediately.\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n	(b) Punctured tyres, empty petrol tank, flat battery due to negligence, loss of vehicle’s key or locked key inside the vehicle, by itself, does not constitute to a breakdown and that in such an event when the Owner’s 24 hours Emergency Service is called upon to respond to such occurrence, the Hirer shall bear the cost of such response at S$50 per trip.(c) Punctured and damaged tyres that cannot be reused will be charged accordingly from S$80-S$200 per tyre. Batteries that cannot be charged back to full capacity will need to be replaced and Hirer is liable to pay $90-$130 for the replacement battery. Lost keys will need to be replaced and the replacement fee, depending on the type of key, is payable by the Hirer. Replacements for all of the above have to be done at a workshop of the Owner’s choice. Should the Hirer choose to do the replacements elsewhere, the Hirer will be liable for any additional damages should the replace ments be unfit/unsuitable for the vehicle.\r\n	</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>	\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="rental col-md-12 col-xs-12">\r\n	<div class="para"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n	<div class="policy-txt">\r\n	<div>\r\n	10 (a) The full rental cost is calculated on the basis of either daily, weekly or monthly rental charges, together with a refundable deposit as stated in the front page of the rental agreement. These are payable in advance on delivery of the vehicle to the Hirer.\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n	(b) In the case of a hire period exceeding one (1) month, the Hirer shall pay the Owner the following monthly rental in advance on the same day as the first rental payment was made.\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n	(c) In the event where the Hirer fails to return the Vehicle on the expiration of this rental Agreement, i.e. where the Vehice is not returned to the location or date as specified overleaf; or if any cheque given by the Hirer to the Owner for payment of rental in advance is dishonoured on presentment for payment or if the Hirer fails to make payment of the rental in advance as provided in the above Clause 10a or 10b; or where the Owner in his discretion extend the hire period without the Hirer paying the full rental in advance as provided in Clause 10a or 10b, whichever is applicable, then without prejudice to other rights of the Owner, the Hirer shall be liable to pay the Owner rental calculated on a daily basis rate and the rate chargeable shall be as stipulated overleaf. In addition, the Owner may, at his discretion, choose to make a demand  under Clause 1 to repossess the vehicle. The Owner will not be liable for any damages and the Hirer will be liable for all costs and expenses incurred, as stipulated under Clauses 2-4. Further to that, the Owner may choose to terminate the existing rental agreement and the security deposit will not be refunded to the Hirer.\r\n	</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>	\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container medium-container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="policy-txt"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n<div class="policy-txt"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n<div class="policy-txt"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n<div class="policy-txt"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n<div class="policy-txt"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54" src="http://vinsmotor-webinno.stag-innov8te.com//wp-content/uploads/2016/05/policy.png" alt="policy" width="24" height="20" /></div>\r\n<div class="policy-txt"><img class="alignnon